x4codes.hlp: Atomic Weapons Establishment (AWE), Aldermaston, United Kingdom

x4codes.shortRef: Prog: U.K. report to EANDC, No.126 (1970)

x4freetext: -ELASTIC AND INELASTIC SCATTERING OF NEUTRONS IN THE
ENERGY RANGE 1.0 TO 5.0 MEV BY NATURAL MOLYBDENUM.-
AWRE 6 MV VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR.
T(P,N)HE-3 REACTION, TRITIUM GAS TARGET WITH
A 0.0003 CM THICK MO ENTRANCE FOIL AND 760 TORR GAS
PRESSURE.
THE INCIDENT NEUTRON  ENERGIES VARIED FROM 1 TO 5 MEV
ENERGY SPREADS ON SOURCE NEUTRON ENERGIES VARIED FROM
50 KEV AT 1.0 MEV NEUTRON ENERGY, TO 30 KEV AT 3.0
MEV, TO 20 KEV AT 5.0 MEV.  THESE ENERGY SPREADS ARE
ALMOST ENTIRELY DUE TO INCIDENT PROTON ENERGY LOSS IN
THE GAS CELL.
RIGHT CYLINDER OF NATURAL MO, 2.0 CM. O.D., 1.20 CM
I.D. AND 4.99 CM LONG. PURITY BETTER THAN 99 PERC.
TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATH = 1.747 M,
A SECOND TIME OF FLIGHT SPECTROMETER, VIEWING THE GAS
TARGET AT A FIXED ANGLE, WAS USED AS A MONITOR TO
COMPARE NEUTRON YIELDS AT DIFFERENT ANGLES.
LIQUID SCINTILLATOR (NE213) AND MEASUREMENT
OF DETECTOR EFFICIENCY WITH N-ENERGY, SEE TOWLE AND
WALL, NUCL.PHYS.A118(1968)500.   THE EXTRAPOLATION OF
THE COUNTER EFFICIENCY CURVE FROM 4.2 TO 5.0 MEV WAS
GUIDED BY PAST EXPERIENCE RUNS USING D-D N-SOURCE.
IN ADDITION TO THE MONITOR TOF SPECTROMETER
TWO LONG COUNTERS WERE ALSO USED AS FLUX MONITOR.
MOST OF THE DATA ANALYSIS, INCLUDING PEAK AREAS,
INELASTIC CONTINUUM ANALYSIS AND REPETITIVE
CALCULATIONS WERE DONE ON A PDP-7 COMPUTER.
HORSLEY, NUCL.DATA 2(1966)243,
THE SCATTERING AT 45 DEG FROM THE POLYTHENE SAMPLE WAS
MEASURED.
THE WELL-KNOWN SCATTERED N-GROUP
ENERGIES FROM IRON WERE USED FOR THE TIME CALIBRATION
THE INTENSION OF THIS WORK IS TO PROVIDE DETAILED
EXPERIMENTAL DATA IN THE RANGE 1.0 TO 5.0 MEV PRIOR TO
AN EVALUATION OF SCATTERING CROSS SECTION FOR NATURAL
MO, NO ATTEMPT HAS BEEN MADE TO COMPARE THE DATA WITH
THEORETICAL PREDICTIONS.
INTEGRATED.
NEUTRONS.
FROM TABLE 6,PAG. 22 OF THE PUBLICATION.
ERRORS ARE GIVEN.

x4freetext: FROM ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION RUNS,
INTEGRATED.
NEUTRONS.
SINCE NATURAL MO CONTAINS SEVEN ISOTOPES WITH DIFFER-
ENT LEVEL SCHEMES, INELASTICALLY SCATTERED NEUTRON
SPECTRA ARE COMPLEX. THESE SPECTRA WERE SPLIT
INTO DISCRETE GROUPS OF LEVELS AND AN INELASTIC
CONTINUUM. EACH GROUP OF LEVELS CONTAINED ONE OR MORE
LEVELS FROM ONE OR MORE ISOTOPES.
E-LVL QUANTITY GIVEN BELOW WAS CALCULATED FROM THE
ENERGIES OF THE INDIVIDUAL LEVELS WEIGHTED BY THE
APPROPRIATE ISOTOPE ABUNDANCES.
